INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('HCSB', 'Zephaniah', 1, 1, 'The word of the LORD that came to Zephaniah son of Cushi, son of Gedaliah, son of Amariah, son of Hezekiah, in the days of Josiah son of Amon, king of Judah.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('HCSB', 'Zephaniah', 1, 2, 'I will completely sweep away everything from the face of the earth-- [this is] the LORD''s declaration.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('HCSB', 'Zephaniah', 1, 3, 'I will sweep away man and animal; I will sweep away the birds of the sky and the fish of the sea, and the ruins along with the wicked. I will cut off mankind from the face of the earth-- the LORD''s declaration.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('HCSB', 'Zephaniah', 1, 4, 'I will stretch out My hand against Judah and against all the residents of Jerusalem. I will cut off from this place every vestige of Baal, the names of the pagan priests along with the priests;');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('HCSB', 'Zephaniah', 1, 5, 'those who bow in worship on the rooftops to the heavenly host; those who bow and pledge loyalty to the LORD but also pledge loyalty to Milcom;');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('HCSB', 'Zephaniah', 1, 6, 'and those who turn back from following the LORD, who do not seek the LORD or inquire of Him.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('HCSB', 'Zephaniah', 1, 7, 'Be silent in the presence of the Lord God, for the Day of the LORD is near. Indeed, the LORD has prepared a sacrifice; He has consecrated His guests.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('HCSB', 'Zephaniah', 1, 8, 'On the day of the LORD''s sacrifice I will punish the officials, the king''s sons, and all who are dressed in foreign clothing.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('HCSB', 'Zephaniah', 1, 9, 'On that day I will punish all who skip over the threshold, who fill their master''s house with violence and deceit.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('HCSB', 'Zephaniah', 1, 10, 'On that day-- the LORD''s declaration-- there will be an outcry from the Fish Gate, a wailing from the Second District, and a loud crashing from the hills.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('HCSB', 'Zephaniah', 1, 11, 'Wail, you residents of the Hollow, for all the merchants will be silenced; all those loaded with silver will be cut off.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('HCSB', 'Zephaniah', 1, 12, 'And at that time I will search Jerusalem with lamps and punish the men who settle down comfortably, who say to themselves: The LORD will not do good or evil.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('HCSB', 'Zephaniah', 1, 13, 'Their wealth will become plunder and their houses a ruin. They will build houses but never live [in them], plant vineyards but never drink their wine.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('HCSB', 'Zephaniah', 1, 14, 'The great Day of the LORD is near, near and rapidly approaching. Listen, the Day of the LORD-- there the warrior''s cry is bitter.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('HCSB', 'Zephaniah', 1, 15, 'That day is a day of wrath, a day of trouble and distress, a day of destruction and desolation, a day of darkness and gloom, a day of clouds and blackness,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('HCSB', 'Zephaniah', 1, 16, 'a day of trumpet [blast] and battle cry against the fortified cities, and against the high corner towers.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('HCSB', 'Zephaniah', 1, 17, 'I will bring distress on mankind, and they will walk like the blind because they have sinned against the LORD. Their blood will be poured out like dust and their flesh like dung.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('HCSB', 'Zephaniah', 1, 18, 'Their silver and their gold will not be able to rescue them on the day of the LORD''s wrath. The whole earth will be consumed by the fire of His jealousy. For He will make a complete, yes, a horrifying end of all the inhabitants of the earth.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('HCSB', 'Zephaniah', 2, 1, 'Gather yourselves together; gather together, undesirable nation,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('HCSB', 'Zephaniah', 2, 2, 'before the decree takes effect and the day passes like chaff, before the burning of the LORD''s anger overtakes you, before the day of the LORD''s anger overtakes you.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('HCSB', 'Zephaniah', 2, 3, 'Seek the LORD, all you humble of the earth, who carry out what He commands. Seek righteousness, seek humility; perhaps you will be concealed on the day of the LORD''s anger.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('HCSB', 'Zephaniah', 2, 4, 'For Gaza will be abandoned, and Ashkelon will become a ruin. Ashdod will be driven out at noon, and Ekron will be uprooted.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('HCSB', 'Zephaniah', 2, 5, 'Woe, inhabitants of the seacoast, nation of the Cherethites! The word of the LORD is against you, Canaan, land of the Philistines: I will destroy you until there is no one left.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('HCSB', 'Zephaniah', 2, 6, 'The seacoast will become pasturelands with caves for shepherds and folds for sheep.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('HCSB', 'Zephaniah', 2, 7, 'The coastland will belong to the remnant of the house of Judah; they will find pasture there. They will lie down in the evening among the houses of Ashkelon, for the LORD their God will return to them and restore their fortunes.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('HCSB', 'Zephaniah', 2, 8, 'I have heard the taunting of Moab and the insults of the Ammonites, who have taunted My people and threatened their territory.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('HCSB', 'Zephaniah', 2, 9, 'Therefore, as I live-- the declaration of the LORD of Hosts, the God of Israel-- Moab will be like Sodom and the Ammonites like Gomorrah-- a place overgrown with weeds, a salt pit, and a perpetual wasteland. The remnant of My people will plunder them; the remainder of My nation will dispossess them.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('HCSB', 'Zephaniah', 2, 10, 'This is what they get for their pride, because they have taunted and acted arrogantly against the people of the LORD of Hosts.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('HCSB', 'Zephaniah', 2, 11, 'The LORD will be terrifying to them when He starves all the gods of the earth. Then all the distant coastlands of the nations will bow in worship to Him, each in its own place.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('HCSB', 'Zephaniah', 2, 12, 'You Cushites will also be slain by My sword.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('HCSB', 'Zephaniah', 2, 13, 'He will also stretch out His hand against the north and destroy Assyria; He will make Nineveh a desolate ruin, dry as the desert.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('HCSB', 'Zephaniah', 2, 14, 'Herds will lie down in the middle of it, every kind of wild animal. Both the desert owl and the screech owl will roost in the capitals of its pillars. [Their] calls will sound from the window, but devastation will be on the threshold, for He will expose the cedar work.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('HCSB', 'Zephaniah', 2, 15, 'This is the self-assured city that lives in security, that thinks to herself: I am, and there is no one besides me. What a desolation she has become, a place for wild animals to lie down! Everyone who passes by her jeers and shakes his fist.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('HCSB', 'Zephaniah', 3, 1, 'Woe to the city that is rebellious and defiled, the oppressive city!');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('HCSB', 'Zephaniah', 3, 2, 'She has not obeyed; she has not accepted discipline. She has not trusted in the LORD; she has not drawn near to her God.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('HCSB', 'Zephaniah', 3, 3, 'The princes within her are roaring lions; her judges are wolves of the night, which leave nothing for the morning.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('HCSB', 'Zephaniah', 3, 4, 'Her prophets are reckless-- treacherous men. Her priests profane the sanctuary; they do violence to instruction.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('HCSB', 'Zephaniah', 3, 5, 'The righteous LORD is in her; He does no wrong. He applies His justice morning by morning; He does not fail at dawn, yet the one who does wrong knows no shame.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('HCSB', 'Zephaniah', 3, 6, 'I have cut off nations; their corner towers are destroyed. I have laid waste their streets, with no one to pass through. Their cities lie devastated, without a person, without an inhabitant.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('HCSB', 'Zephaniah', 3, 7, 'I thought: You will certainly fear Me and accept correction. Then her dwelling place would not be cut off [based on] all that I had allocated to her. However, they became more corrupt in all their actions.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('HCSB', 'Zephaniah', 3, 8, 'Therefore, wait for Me-- the LORD''s declaration-- until the day I rise up for plunder. For My decision is to gather nations, to assemble kingdoms, in order to pour out My indignation on them, all My burning anger; for the whole earth will be consumed by the fire of My jealousy.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('HCSB', 'Zephaniah', 3, 9, 'For I will then restore pure speech to the peoples so that all of them may call on the name of Yahweh and serve Him with a single purpose.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('HCSB', 'Zephaniah', 3, 10, 'From beyond the rivers of Cush My supplicants, My dispersed people, will bring an offering to Me.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('HCSB', 'Zephaniah', 3, 11, 'On that day you will not be put to shame because of everything you have done in rebelling against Me. For then I will remove your boastful braggarts from among you, and you will never again be haughty on My holy mountain.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('HCSB', 'Zephaniah', 3, 12, 'I will leave a meek and humble people among you, and they will trust in the name of Yahweh.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('HCSB', 'Zephaniah', 3, 13, 'The remnant of Israel will no longer do wrong or tell lies; a deceitful tongue will not be found in their mouths. But they will pasture and lie down, with nothing to make [them] afraid.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('HCSB', 'Zephaniah', 3, 14, 'Sing for joy, Daughter Zion; shout loudly, Israel! Be glad and rejoice with all [your] heart, Daughter Jerusalem!');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('HCSB', 'Zephaniah', 3, 15, 'The LORD has removed your punishment; He has turned back your enemy. The King of Israel, the LORD, is among you; you need no longer fear harm.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('HCSB', 'Zephaniah', 3, 16, 'On that day it will be said to Jerusalem: "Do not fear; Zion, do not let your hands grow weak.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('HCSB', 'Zephaniah', 3, 17, 'The LORD your God is among you, a warrior who saves. He will rejoice over you with gladness. He will bring [you] quietness with His love. He will delight in you with shouts of joy."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('HCSB', 'Zephaniah', 3, 18, 'I will gather those who have been driven from the appointed festivals; [They will be] a tribute from you, and reproach [on her].');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('HCSB', 'Zephaniah', 3, 19, 'Yes, at that time I will deal with all who afflict you. I will save the lame and gather the scattered; I will make those who were disgraced throughout the earth receive praise and fame.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('HCSB', 'Zephaniah', 3, 20, 'At that time I will bring you back, yes, at the time I will gather you. I will make you famous and praiseworthy among all the peoples of the earth, when I restore your fortunes before your eyes. Yahweh has spoken.');
